{"tid":999674,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"華為之後換戰它？ 澳網路專家矛頭指向微信","createTime":"2019-01-29T01:23:42.000Z","updateTime":"2019-01-29T03:54:58.000Z","uid":39464,"like":42,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":22,"replies":[{"pid":"f9564f82a4466f658793bd3991e651b86bf6cf3b","tid":999674,"uid":39464,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-01-29T01:23:42.000Z","msg":"〔即時新聞／綜合報導〕中國華為近來成為西方社會的眾矢之的，被排除在5G建設之外，首席財務長孟晚舟還被捕，今天外媒報導，又有一間中國企業被外國專家盯上，就是不少人使用的社交平台微信（WeChat）<br />\n<br />\n《BBC中文網》報導，最近有澳洲戰略政策研究所的國際網絡政策研究室警告，中國可能透過微信影響澳洲聯邦選舉，像是推動公眾輿論，而澳洲有150萬的微信用戶，他們可能會收到錯誤的消息，原因在於微信受到中國的控制。<br />\n<br />\n報導指出，澳洲的微信新聞帳號去年被發現，完全沒有關於中國政治與外交的消息，此外，與中國統戰部有聯繫的澳洲公民，則在2017年一次選戰中，大力批判對中國立場強硬的候選人。<br />\n<br />\n報導指出，聯邦政府與臉書、推特等社交平台有所溝通，避免有人惡意散布不實消息，但澳洲選舉委員會表示，他們沒有和微信的母公司騰訊溝通過。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://m.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/2686050\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fm.ltn.com.tw%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fbreakingnews%2F2686050&d=AMPtd42ADahZ7WU%2BVKQ9tQHuyxefasl%2FZxVLfhQSBMM%3D&h=f1ad4e2e\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=http%3A%2F%2Fm.ltn.com.tw%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fbreakingnews%2F2686050&h=3ab45663\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">http://m.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/2686050</a>"},{"pid":"50e8d19b384f183e49d84eedfcff30b039aed951","tid":999674,"uid":121146,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-01-29T01:25:11.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1d3f1cbb29d33293f5741ee44624c5a48b3b357e","tid":999674,"uid":150347,"like":5,"dislike":0,"score":5,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-01-29T01:27:10.000Z","msg":"全面封殺，點搞阿<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/nosee.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/nosee.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9cb578bea9c5979094c49f19f0a7f8ef45e24ed6","tid":999674,"uid":18477,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score"